296
00:27:08,799 --> 00:27:10,029
Fine, I'll do it.

297
00:27:11,299 --> 00:27:12,339
I'll clean up.

298
00:27:28,619 --> 00:27:31,420
I'm sorry, but who are you
and why are you in there?

299
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:33,390
Is it morning?

300
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:48,839
Are you kidding me?

301
00:27:54,079 --> 00:27:55,509
The spacing...

302
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:57,950
He's Mr. Dawn.

303
00:28:09,029 --> 00:28:11,130
- What on earth is this?
- Is there...

304
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:14,529
Gosh.

305
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:18,329
I meant to clean up, but I forgot.

306
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:19,940
Let me clean up.

307
00:28:20,839 --> 00:28:22,670
Didn't you rent this place
during the night?

308
00:28:23,309 --> 00:28:24,769
Yes, until 4am.

309
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:26,480
Look at the time now.

310
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:29,250
I'm busy as it is.

311
00:28:30,549 --> 00:28:32,319
I get to work at 8:30,

312
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:34,920
so please clean up before then.
Got it?

313
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,089
8:30am.

314
00:28:53,099 --> 00:28:55,440
Leave it open so that at least
one more person can hear it.

315
00:29:29,210 --> 00:29:30,240
Seo Woo!

316
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:34,809
I see you didn't get lost.

317
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,410
We have a recital today.

318
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:39,549
- Let me help.
- It's fine.

319
00:29:42,420 --> 00:29:44,950
My grandmother cared
for these trees for 30 years.

320
00:29:45,519 --> 00:29:48,660
All by herself? That's incredible.

321
00:29:48,660 --> 00:29:51,660
She devotes her time and love
to every living being.

322
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:54,200
How many will be here today?

323
00:29:54,599 --> 00:29:55,829
The floor will be filled...

324
00:29:55,829 --> 00:29:57,470
and the yard can
accommodate more people.

325
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:00,339
I didn't expect this to be
such a grand event.

326
00:30:02,009 --> 00:30:03,809
Consider it as a family event.

327
00:30:04,539 --> 00:30:06,480
During her days as a diplomat,

328
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:09,710
Grandmother sponsored children
who were gifted in music...

329
00:30:09,710 --> 00:30:12,349
and held a recital for them.
She must have liked doing it.

330
00:30:14,150 --> 00:30:16,390
She did something remarkable then.

331
00:30:17,150 --> 00:30:18,150
Tell me about it.

332
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:21,819
The money she contributed
could've bought me a building.

333
00:30:23,930 --> 00:30:27,099
Grandma insists
we're one big family,

334
00:30:27,329 --> 00:30:28,569
but how can I accept that?

335
00:30:29,329 --> 00:30:31,529
Only my uncle is family to me...

336
00:30:31,529 --> 00:30:33,500
and the others are mere strangers.

337
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:35,809
Why is your uncle your only family?

338
00:30:36,509 --> 00:30:38,740
Because he's handsome and competent.

339
00:30:42,150 --> 00:30:44,450
Don't tell me you believed that.
I was only joking.

340
00:30:44,779 --> 00:30:47,980
My uncle and I
share an emotional story.

341
00:30:51,490 --> 00:30:54,160
I've never met anyone
who sponsors others before.

342
00:30:54,559 --> 00:30:55,960
Your grandmother is an inspiration.

343
00:30:56,089 --> 00:30:59,559
So how about it?
Do I seem more trustworthy now?

344
00:31:01,099 --> 00:31:02,529
That being said...

345
00:31:06,039 --> 00:31:08,240
Can you record
some of Kim Ji Su's words?

346
00:31:08,710 --> 00:31:11,369
- But why?
- How should I know?

347
00:31:11,710 --> 00:31:13,680
I don't even know
what this device is for either.

348
00:31:15,210 --> 00:31:16,480
With this,

349
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,619
the voice will sound like
it's coming from right next to you.

350
00:31:18,619 --> 00:31:22,690
Yes, he must want
a vivid recording of her voice.

351
00:31:23,049 --> 00:31:24,549
I will only do this
after you tell me...

352
00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:26,220
what it's for and who asked of this.

353
00:31:26,220 --> 00:31:28,559
Well, this someone...

354
00:31:29,690 --> 00:31:31,660
- yearns for her.
- Who does?

355
00:31:32,460 --> 00:31:33,900
That's all you need to know.

356
00:31:35,869 --> 00:31:38,529
How can I record her voice
when we're not even friends?

357
00:31:38,529 --> 00:31:39,940
Who says you have to
be her friend to do that?

358
00:31:40,569 --> 00:31:43,470
Buy more bowls from her
and meet her in the process.

359
00:31:43,470 --> 00:31:45,839
Chat about meaningless things
for a while,

360
00:31:45,839 --> 00:31:49,180
tell her she has a nice voice,
and get her to record something.

361
00:31:49,410 --> 00:31:51,950
Who records someone's voice
because they like the tone of it?

362
00:31:52,380 --> 00:31:54,519
This isn't like getting
someone's number.

363
00:31:54,519 --> 00:31:57,220
"I think you have a beautiful voice.
Could I please record it?"

364
00:31:58,990 --> 00:32:00,259
Just do what I ask.

365
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,220
A record player?

366
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:36,150
That looks really old.

367
00:33:37,349 --> 00:33:38,859
Does it work?

368
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:05,819
What does he have with Kim Ji Su?

369
00:34:06,079 --> 00:34:07,619
Children like islands.

370
00:34:09,949 --> 00:34:11,090
Who?

371
00:34:11,150 --> 00:34:13,719
You asked about me and Kim Ji Su.

372
00:34:17,789 --> 00:34:19,860
How long have you known each other?

373
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:52,130
The only two Korean kids
in Norway...

374
00:34:52,130 --> 00:34:55,429
met when they were young.

375
00:34:55,769 --> 00:34:57,429
They went to middle school,

376
00:34:58,230 --> 00:34:59,739
and then high school.

377
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:03,769
They met as soon as the sun rose,

378
00:36:03,869 --> 00:36:05,599
and parted when the sun set.

379
00:36:07,239 --> 00:36:10,309
During the white night,
they were together for 24 hours.

380
00:36:13,679 --> 00:36:15,550
They thought it a pity
when the sun set.

381
00:36:19,679 --> 00:36:21,849
- Ga.
- Gya.

382
00:36:22,119 --> 00:36:24,519
- Geo.
- Gyeo.

383
00:36:24,590 --> 00:36:26,789
- Go.
- Gyo.

384
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:28,820
- Gu.
- Gyu.

385
00:36:31,059 --> 00:36:32,800
"A single leaf,"

386
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:35,329
"without a sound,"

387
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:38,699
"landed softly on my shoulder."

388
00:36:39,139 --> 00:36:42,539
"The universe
put a hand on my body."

389
00:36:42,969 --> 00:36:44,869
- "It's so light."
- "It's so light."

390
00:36:46,239 --> 00:36:49,650
Their own language became a secret
and brought them close.

391
00:36:50,510 --> 00:36:52,079
They like islands.

392
00:37:00,860 --> 00:37:02,219
Who are you?

393
00:37:02,260 --> 00:37:03,989
Introduce yourself first.

394
00:37:04,130 --> 00:37:06,000
Then I'll explain our relationship.

395
00:37:11,199 --> 00:37:12,699
Why are you hiding?

396
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:16,570
Why do you need
a recording of her voice?

397
00:37:16,570 --> 00:37:19,380
Are you not going to meet Kim Ji Su?

398
00:37:25,309 --> 00:37:26,320
What about what I asked?

399
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,619
I don't know.

400
00:37:27,619 --> 00:37:30,449
She might do it,
but then she might not.

401
00:37:30,789 --> 00:37:33,360
Why did you ask me
to do such a thing?

402
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,360
Why do you even want a recording?

403
00:37:37,690 --> 00:37:39,360
A recording is enough.

404
00:37:40,159 --> 00:37:41,530
I just need...

405
00:37:41,530 --> 00:37:43,000
I just need...

406
00:37:43,300 --> 00:37:45,030
a piece of Ji Su.

407
00:37:46,570 --> 00:37:49,840
Where are you right now?

408
00:37:52,739 --> 00:37:53,940
Find me.

409
00:38:35,690 --> 00:38:39,159
I just need a piece of Ji Su.

410
00:38:57,170 --> 00:38:58,409
Hello.

411
00:38:59,039 --> 00:39:00,039
Hi.

412
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:02,710
Are you done?

413
00:39:03,179 --> 00:39:06,480
No, my eyes are tired.
The light's not working.

414
00:39:16,260 --> 00:39:18,090
It just takes a few slaps.

415
00:39:18,090 --> 00:39:20,400
I'll tell the manager later on.

416
00:39:36,980 --> 00:39:38,010
Oh, dear.

417
00:39:47,989 --> 00:39:48,989
Gosh.

418
00:39:50,230 --> 00:39:51,960
I can't see in the dark.

419
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:55,199
I can't find my way even in cinemas.

420
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:57,300
- Can you see?
- Yes.

421
00:39:57,969 --> 00:39:59,369
I'm used to the dark.

422
00:40:04,570 --> 00:40:07,409
- Come this way.
- I see that much.

423
00:40:10,110 --> 00:40:11,280
Find me.

424
00:40:17,690 --> 00:40:19,050
Excuse me.

425
00:40:19,590 --> 00:40:21,860
From what time
did you rent the studio?

426
00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:23,789
I heard it was empty,
so I came early.

427
00:40:23,989 --> 00:40:25,389
At about 7pm?

428
00:40:25,489 --> 00:40:28,530
You were here all evening, then?

429
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:29,929
Yes.

430
00:40:32,170 --> 00:40:34,599
I thought I heard a similar voice.

431
00:40:35,769 --> 00:40:38,210
He was hiding,
so I didn't see his face.

432
00:40:40,179 --> 00:40:41,409
- Hiding?
- Yes.

433
00:40:41,409 --> 00:40:43,309
The manager's farm.

434
00:40:43,309 --> 00:40:45,349
I was there because
she asked me to record something.

435
00:40:45,349 --> 00:40:48,250
It was a room
with an old record player.

436
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:51,789
There was no room to hide,
but he hid when he talked to me.

437
00:40:51,789 --> 00:40:54,019
Until when did Grandma live in Oslo?

438
00:40:54,159 --> 00:40:56,690
From 1997 to 2005.

439
00:40:57,590 --> 00:40:59,230
What did he say?

440
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:02,260
He told me to find him.

441
00:41:03,269 --> 00:41:05,099
What did you say
that made him say that?

442
00:41:05,099 --> 00:41:07,500
I asked where he was
and he told me to find him.

443
00:41:07,500 --> 00:41:08,969
Why did you ask where he was?

444
00:41:08,969 --> 00:41:11,869
Because he was talking to me
from a hiding place.

445
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:15,480
How strange.

446
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,349
It was very strange.

447
00:41:17,780 --> 00:41:19,980
So many strange things
happen these days.

448
00:41:19,980 --> 00:41:22,519
People I don't know
make way into my life,

449
00:41:22,519 --> 00:41:24,389
and ask for strange favors.

450
00:41:28,119 --> 00:41:29,730
You have to work.

451
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,260
Time is money here.

452
00:41:33,500 --> 00:41:34,699
Goodbye.

453
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:43,010
Do you understand...

454
00:41:45,340 --> 00:41:49,139
someone who wants a voice recording
because he misses someone?

455
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:52,980
It's not common,

456
00:41:53,079 --> 00:41:55,019
but I kind of understand.

457
00:41:57,590 --> 00:42:00,389
Keeping a photo
and keeping a recording.

458
00:42:00,389 --> 00:42:02,119
I don't see the difference.

459
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,329
Goodbye.

460
00:42:22,750 --> 00:42:25,110
- I could do it.
- Don't do it.

461
00:42:25,309 --> 00:42:26,519
The woman's weird.

462
00:42:27,380 --> 00:42:30,190
Why would a woman sell bowls?

463
00:42:30,519 --> 00:42:32,389
- Get her recording.
- Don't.

464
00:42:32,389 --> 00:42:33,960
It's all a con.

465
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:36,130
Seo Woo's the idiot
for getting involved.

466
00:42:37,289 --> 00:42:38,730
Give her your name.

467
00:42:38,889 --> 00:42:41,699
Who's the guy? One of
my classmates who married...

468
00:42:41,699 --> 00:42:42,769
Darn you.

469
00:42:42,769 --> 00:42:44,329
Put your dirty bowls in the sink.

470
00:42:44,329 --> 00:42:47,269
I finished doing the bowls.
My gosh.

471
00:42:49,039 --> 00:42:51,710
Should I record her voice or not?

472
00:42:55,610 --> 00:42:59,380
A piece of a piece
of a piece of a piece

473
00:42:59,579 --> 00:43:01,449
A piece of a piece

474
00:43:10,289 --> 00:43:13,530
You should open the windows
once in a while when the sun is out.

475
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:15,900
Don't keep the curtains closed.

476
00:43:16,469 --> 00:43:18,199
Did it also rain all day there?

477
00:43:18,570 --> 00:43:20,739
The nearby mill
got flooded with water.

478
00:43:20,739 --> 00:43:23,769
And the same happened
with the boiler room and farm.

479
00:43:24,239 --> 00:43:27,610
We're the only ones who are okay
because we're located up the hill.

480
00:43:28,679 --> 00:43:32,179
Seo Woo,
I saw a lot of young people...

