00:46:45,070 --> 00:46:46,070
(Prescription)

527
00:46:55,179 --> 00:46:57,789
(Prescription)

528
00:47:00,119 --> 00:47:01,559
It's a prescription.

529
00:47:01,820 --> 00:47:03,860
Yes, I know
what kind of medicine that is.

530
00:47:05,590 --> 00:47:08,599
I also visited a psychiatrist once.

531
00:47:08,599 --> 00:47:11,400
These days, it's very common
to see a psychiatrist.

532
00:47:17,309 --> 00:47:18,610
Where should I write it down?

533
00:47:20,579 --> 00:47:22,380
I'll send it to you via text.

534
00:47:24,309 --> 00:47:27,719
Oh, right.
Why didn't I think of that?

535
00:47:30,219 --> 00:47:32,119
Every time I feel frustrated,

536
00:47:32,119 --> 00:47:34,159
I go to the highest place
in the neighborhood.

537
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:38,659
It feels better
when you look down at the view.

538
00:47:38,659 --> 00:47:41,760
They say astronauts come back with
a different view of the world...

539
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:43,530
once they return from outer space.

540
00:47:43,530 --> 00:47:45,099
I heard their worries
becomes so minuscule.

541
00:47:52,010 --> 00:47:53,610
That's why I sell bowls.

542
00:47:54,679 --> 00:47:55,880
After I saw a psychiatrist,

543
00:47:56,480 --> 00:47:58,110
I felt like I should do something.

544
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:00,619
So I uploaded
a few of my best bowls.

545
00:48:01,050 --> 00:48:02,420
And when I delivered
those bowls to you,

546
00:48:02,420 --> 00:48:04,420
it was my first time coming out
in three months.

547
00:48:07,920 --> 00:48:08,920
Just a second.

548
00:48:17,170 --> 00:48:18,230
What?

549
00:48:18,230 --> 00:48:21,039
You need the alphabet.

550
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:24,539
Consonants, vowels, and sentences.

551
00:48:24,539 --> 00:48:27,179
What kind of sentences?
You need to be more clear.

552
00:48:27,340 --> 00:48:28,610
I'll send you an email.

553
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:30,550
I probably won't get it.

554
00:48:31,210 --> 00:48:34,719
Hey, just check your email.
Then you'll get what I mean.

555
00:48:34,849 --> 00:48:36,590
Refer to the email
before you record her voice.

556
00:48:39,590 --> 00:48:40,659
What was that?

557
00:50:13,349 --> 00:50:14,380
Let's go outside.

558
00:51:26,460 --> 00:51:28,889
Ha Won, look at the ceiling.

559
00:51:31,289 --> 00:51:32,460
It'll make you feel at ease.

560
00:51:38,300 --> 00:51:39,369
Come in.

561
00:51:46,369 --> 00:51:47,840
Stand in front of the microphone.

562
00:51:48,980 --> 00:51:49,980
Me?

563
00:51:52,909 --> 00:51:54,619
Say whatever you want.

564
00:51:56,550 --> 00:51:58,820
- And then what?
- I'll record it...

565
00:51:58,820 --> 00:52:02,059
and sell it at an expensive price
to whomever that misses you.

566
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:04,989
No one misses me.

567
00:52:07,059 --> 00:52:10,630
I'm sure there's always at least
one person who misses us.

568
00:52:13,769 --> 00:52:16,610
- I'm not sure.
- Just think of it comfortably.

569
00:52:17,170 --> 00:52:19,110
You don't need to do it
if you don't want to.

570
00:52:23,949 --> 00:52:25,550
Will you show me how to do it?

571
00:52:27,550 --> 00:52:31,420
First, you can begin
with the alphabet.

572
00:52:32,119 --> 00:52:33,989
You can start
once I give you the signal.

573
00:52:41,900 --> 00:52:42,929
Ga.

574
00:52:47,039 --> 00:52:48,070
Gya.

575
00:52:48,739 --> 00:52:49,739
Geo.

576
00:52:50,539 --> 00:52:51,570
- Gyeo.
- Gyeo.

577
00:52:52,809 --> 00:52:53,840
- Go.
- Go.

578
00:52:54,780 --> 00:52:55,780
- Gyo.
- Gyo.

579
00:52:57,050 --> 00:52:58,150
- Gu.
- Gu.

580
00:52:58,710 --> 00:53:00,550
- Gyu.
- Gyu.

581
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:05,050
I told her to start
with the alphabet.

582
00:53:07,519 --> 00:53:09,690
Let's try saying
a longer sentence this time.

583
00:53:09,989 --> 00:53:11,929
Let me tell you what to say.

584
00:53:15,360 --> 00:53:16,460
A single...

585
00:53:17,400 --> 00:53:18,530
leaf,

586
00:53:20,599 --> 00:53:22,769
without a sound,

587
00:53:23,739 --> 00:53:26,039
landed softly...

588
00:53:27,909 --> 00:53:28,909
(A single leaf, without a sound,
landed softly on my shoulder.)

589
00:53:28,909 --> 00:53:30,309
landed softly on my shoulder.

590
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:36,179
The universe...

591
00:53:36,920 --> 00:53:38,750
put a hand on my body.

592
00:53:41,659 --> 00:53:42,820
It's...

593
00:53:44,829 --> 00:53:46,030
so light.

594
00:53:46,389 --> 00:53:47,730
It's...

595
00:53:48,300 --> 00:53:49,800
so light.

596
00:54:04,179 --> 00:54:07,420
It seems as though
you had those phrases memorized.

597
00:54:08,019 --> 00:54:10,050
While living in Norway,
I studied Korean...

598
00:54:10,050 --> 00:54:12,090
by reading Korean poems and novels.

599
00:54:15,460 --> 00:54:17,690
I'll send you the bowls
once I get home.

600
00:54:17,690 --> 00:54:19,530
Right, the address.

601
00:54:23,130 --> 00:54:25,400
Wait, this is near the cafe.

602
00:54:27,300 --> 00:54:30,369
I haven't been to
my friend's house before, you see.

603
00:54:31,440 --> 00:54:34,079
(Select recipient)

604
00:54:35,679 --> 00:54:36,980
I just sent it.

605
00:54:40,679 --> 00:54:42,480
I'll get going then.

606
00:54:48,420 --> 00:54:52,460
(From Han Seo Woo,
47-341, Okin-dong, Jongno-gu)

607
00:55:16,989 --> 00:55:18,389
It's Ha Won, isn't it?

608
00:55:20,289 --> 00:55:23,630
Is he the one who orchestrated
this whole deal?

609
00:55:27,699 --> 00:55:28,860
It's Ha Won, isn't it?

610
00:55:30,869 --> 00:55:34,170
Is he the one who orchestrated
this whole deal?

611
00:55:35,400 --> 00:55:36,869
I don't know who that is.

612
00:55:36,869 --> 00:55:38,340
The address you just sent me.

613
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:40,880
Only Ha Won and I know it.

614
00:55:54,289 --> 00:55:55,820
I don't know who that is.

615
00:55:55,820 --> 00:55:57,630
What about this address?

616
00:55:58,659 --> 00:56:00,130
Who lives here?

617
00:56:00,130 --> 00:56:01,829
My manager.

618
00:56:01,829 --> 00:56:04,199
What's this manager's name?

619
00:56:04,199 --> 00:56:05,929
Moon Sun Ho.

620
00:56:07,670 --> 00:56:09,099
I guess I was wrong.

621
00:56:10,070 --> 00:56:12,469
Well, even I find it absurd too.

622
00:56:12,469 --> 00:56:14,510
My mind just
jumped to a conclusion...

623
00:56:14,940 --> 00:56:16,579
when it doesn't make sense.

624
00:56:17,179 --> 00:56:19,250
Are you all right?

625
00:56:28,719 --> 00:56:29,719
Good luck then.

626
00:56:48,679 --> 00:56:49,710
Seo Woo.

627
00:56:50,750 --> 00:56:51,909
Who was that?

628
00:56:51,909 --> 00:56:53,650
My heart halted just now.

629
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:55,980
This is terrible.

630
00:56:55,980 --> 00:56:57,250
The number of lies I told today...

631
00:56:57,250 --> 00:56:58,519
would equal to the number
I'd say in a lifetime.

632
00:56:58,820 --> 00:57:01,420
Who was that woman?

633
00:57:01,719 --> 00:57:03,119
Kim Ji Su.

634
00:57:06,190 --> 00:57:08,800
What? Are you insane?

635
00:57:08,860 --> 00:57:10,300
Why did you bring her here?

636
00:57:10,300 --> 00:57:12,300
The answer is Ha Won.

637
00:57:13,000 --> 00:57:17,110
He just told her who he was.

638
00:57:17,110 --> 00:57:20,809
After seeing the address, she
asked if he had put me up to this.

639
00:57:21,280 --> 00:57:22,980
Apparently, only the two of them
know about that address.

640
00:57:22,980 --> 00:57:24,110
Oh, dear.

641
00:57:24,380 --> 00:57:26,280
The phrases Kim Ji Su
fully memorizes...

642
00:57:26,280 --> 00:57:28,179
and the address
she clearly remembers.

643
00:57:28,179 --> 00:57:31,590
It's as if he's begging her
to figure out who he is.

644
00:57:33,289 --> 00:57:36,119
Anyway, it's about time
that guy showed up.

645
00:57:37,190 --> 00:57:38,559
Where is he?

646
00:57:39,860 --> 00:57:42,599
Why would you bring her here though?

647
00:57:42,599 --> 00:57:44,570
Who on earth is Ha Won?

648
00:57:44,599 --> 00:57:45,599
Why do you ask?

649
00:57:45,599 --> 00:57:47,000
He wants me to find him.

650
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:49,269
Ha Won said that to you?

651
00:57:50,369 --> 00:57:52,769
I can't believe this.

652
00:57:52,769 --> 00:57:54,480
No wonder you brought her here.

653
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:57,480
Gosh, unbelievable!

654
00:57:57,480 --> 00:57:59,349
What an idiot.

655
00:58:02,079 --> 00:58:03,789
That's it. I'm done.

656
00:58:03,789 --> 00:58:05,989
I'm done doing
any more of your favors.

657
00:58:07,090 --> 00:58:10,460
A single leaf,

658
00:58:12,789 --> 00:58:15,059
without a sound,

659
00:58:16,230 --> 00:58:17,300
landed...

660
00:58:17,300 --> 00:58:19,570
I'll be done
right after I send this.

661
00:58:20,599 --> 00:58:22,139
softly on my shoulder.

662
00:58:23,170 --> 00:58:24,809
The universe...

663
00:58:24,809 --> 00:58:25,969
Her tone has dropped slightly.

664
00:58:25,969 --> 00:58:27,679
- put a hand on my body.
- Sorry?

665
00:58:27,679 --> 00:58:29,909
It's at about 195Hz...

666
00:58:30,449 --> 00:58:32,309
and 55dB.

667
00:58:32,550 --> 00:58:33,750
It's...

668
00:58:34,579 --> 00:58:36,119
so light.

669
00:58:36,380 --> 00:58:37,550
A depressed tone.

670
00:58:37,550 --> 00:58:38,820
That's right.

671
00:58:43,829 --> 00:58:46,559
Just give me a logical answer.

672
00:58:48,960 --> 00:58:52,929
This recording studio
is connected to a man named Ha Won.

673
00:58:53,300 --> 00:58:55,570
From everything
including the recording sessions,

674
00:58:55,570 --> 00:58:57,869
he had it all planned out
for some time now,

675
00:58:58,210 --> 00:59:00,610
but he keeps himself in the shadows.

676
00:59:00,809 --> 00:59:02,610
I'd call him meticulous.

677
00:59:03,340 --> 00:59:06,179
Everything about him
points to a woman named Kim Ji Su.

678
00:59:06,179 --> 00:59:07,750
He misses her a lot.

679
00:59:07,750 --> 00:59:09,750
However, she's suffering
from depression.

680
00:59:09,750 --> 00:59:11,050
That being said,

681
00:59:14,190 --> 00:59:16,590
what if...

682
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:19,630
I let those two meet?

683
00:59:22,230 --> 00:59:25,599
No, I'm just sticking my head into
where it doesn't belong,

684
00:59:25,599 --> 00:59:26,670
right?

685
00:59:27,239 --> 00:59:29,369
I rarely get involved
in others' business like this.

686
00:59:29,599 --> 00:59:31,869
Why do you wish
to bring them together?

687
00:59:36,179 --> 00:59:37,449
I bet you don't remember...

688
00:59:37,449 --> 00:59:38,880
the first impression
you had of everyone.

689
00:59:39,280 --> 00:59:40,349
Probably not.

690
00:59:41,480 --> 00:59:44,150
Same here. I don't either.

691
00:59:44,789 --> 00:59:48,059
But with some people,
even though it was only in passing,

692
00:59:48,289 --> 00:59:51,059
you remember
how they opened the door,

693
00:59:51,389 --> 00:59:54,500
if they were seated or standing,

694
00:59:54,760 --> 00:59:57,070
and how you first
began your conversation.

695
00:59:57,699 --> 01:00:01,099
With them,
that memory is always vivid.

696
01:00:02,969 --> 01:00:06,510
Like how she walked up the hill...

697
01:00:09,639 --> 01:00:12,579
Those are the people
I rarely forget about.

698
01:00:12,579 --> 01:00:15,750
That's how I felt about Ji Su
which is why I want to help her.

699
01:00:27,829 --> 01:00:30,300
Do you always stare
at people like that?

700
01:00:31,730 --> 01:00:33,030
Was I staring?

701
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:35,139
I found your reason intriguing.

702
01:00:35,199 --> 01:00:36,400
It made sense too.

703
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:37,610
Did it?

704
01:00:39,010 --> 01:00:41,440
The reason why one's heart moves?

705
01:00:43,340 --> 01:00:45,679
You don't know why,
but it just happens.

706
01:00:46,380 --> 01:00:49,849
It's probably due to afterimages
that are stacked upon each other.

707
01:00:49,849 --> 01:00:52,789
Your first impression approach
never occurred to me.

708
01:01:00,030 --> 01:01:02,130
I remember the first time
I saw you though.

709
01:01:09,900 --> 01:01:10,909
Me too.

710
01:01:11,369 --> 01:01:12,969
We met here.

711
01:01:12,969 --> 01:01:15,639
You were in the booth
while I was out here.

712
01:01:29,559 --> 01:01:31,590
I see you don't remember.

713
01:01:31,590 --> 01:01:33,489
I guess I was someone
only you passed by then.

714
01:01:36,559 --> 01:01:39,500
Should I let them meet?

715
01:01:42,139 --> 01:01:44,809
But what if
they both end up suffering?

716
01:01:45,440 --> 01:01:47,139
That's their burden to share.

717
01:02:37,090 --> 01:02:40,130
You should open the windows
once in a while when the sun is out.

718
01:02:40,630 --> 01:02:42,500
Don't keep the curtains closed.

719
01:02:43,300 --> 01:02:44,829
Did it also rain all day there?

720
01:02:45,469 --> 01:02:47,670
The nearby mill
got flooded with water.

721
01:02:47,670 --> 01:02:50,440
And the same happened
with the boiler room and farm.

722
01:02:57,550 --> 01:03:00,550
I don't speak with people
who don't know music.

723
01:03:00,980 --> 01:03:03,050
Sir. The thing is...

724
01:03:03,280 --> 01:03:05,750
Here's the music person.

725
01:03:05,989 --> 01:03:07,989
Since when were you a music person?

726
01:03:07,989 --> 01:03:10,420
You're here. What happened is...

727
01:03:10,420 --> 01:03:12,130
I don't care for the reason.

728
01:03:12,630 --> 01:03:15,230
All you had to do was send a text
saying the recording's canceled.

729
01:03:15,760 --> 01:03:16,800
Am I wrong?

730
01:03:20,269 --> 01:03:23,039
The studio was closed down,

731
01:03:23,039 --> 01:03:25,309
and we assumed all
previous schedules were canceled.

732
01:03:25,309 --> 01:03:26,409
I heard someone reopened it.

733
01:03:26,409 --> 01:03:28,239
Other recordings
were scheduled instead.

734
01:03:28,239 --> 01:03:30,710
Oh, so you'll do those jobs
but not this?

735
01:03:30,849 --> 01:03:33,250
I'll call Mr. Choi right now.

736
01:03:33,409 --> 01:03:35,949
Sir. Sir. Will you just...

737
01:03:38,420 --> 01:03:39,590
Let's do just one take.

738
01:03:40,019 --> 01:03:41,920
I must do it?

739
01:03:41,920 --> 01:03:43,820
Talk to Jin Moo about the mixing.

740
01:03:44,159 --> 01:03:46,659
- Let's cancel today and...
- I'll do it.

741
01:03:48,460 --> 01:03:50,969
I'll discuss the mixing
with Mr. Choi,

742
01:03:50,969 --> 01:03:52,900
- and if it's dreadful...
- Delete the track.

743
01:03:53,570 --> 01:03:54,869
There will be no pay.

744
01:04:03,409 --> 01:04:04,880
This hurts my pride.

745
01:04:06,679 --> 01:04:08,480
Coming back
hurts my pride even more.

746
01:05:23,019 --> 01:05:24,059
Hello.

747
01:05:37,670 --> 01:05:39,269
My goodness.

748
01:05:41,809 --> 01:05:42,809
What?

749
01:05:44,780 --> 01:05:46,579
I'm off to meet Kim Ji Su.

750
01:05:47,420 --> 01:05:48,719
You said you wouldn't do anything.

751
01:05:49,050 --> 01:05:51,590
Tell Ha Won to be there.

752
01:05:52,889 --> 01:05:55,059
Hey. Are you sure about this?

753
01:05:57,019 --> 01:05:58,130
What's gotten into her?

754
01:05:58,789 --> 01:06:01,429
Hey. There's a call for you.

755
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:08,199
- What?
- Sun Ho wants you to call.

756
01:06:08,199 --> 01:06:10,139
You don't pick up
at this time of day.

757
01:06:10,710 --> 01:06:12,769
She freaked out at me,
so it must be urgent.

758
01:06:39,070 --> 01:06:40,840
(Han Seo Woo)

759
01:06:50,039 --> 01:06:51,079
Welcome.

760
01:06:52,010 --> 01:06:53,210
(Han Seo Woo)

761
01:06:53,210 --> 01:06:54,349
Are you looking for someone?

762
01:06:54,679 --> 01:06:56,250
I don't think she's here yet.

763
01:06:57,389 --> 01:06:59,150
Then will you order first?

764
01:07:01,119 --> 01:07:02,159
Sure.

765
01:07:14,139 --> 01:07:15,170
Ji Su.

766
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:18,110
- Ji Su?
- Yes, Seo Woo.

767
01:07:20,510 --> 01:07:22,539
I think I'll be a bit late.

768
01:07:23,780 --> 01:07:25,010
Where are you going?

769
01:07:25,710 --> 01:07:27,309
I think I saw someone.

770
01:07:28,320 --> 01:07:29,949
Someone I should never see.

771
01:07:34,119 --> 01:07:36,159
Is it really someone
you shouldn't see?

772
01:07:38,659 --> 01:07:39,789
Is it Ha Won?

773
01:07:42,659 --> 01:07:44,599
- If you see him...
- I can't ever.

774
01:07:49,869 --> 01:07:50,940
Don't turn around.

775
01:08:06,050 --> 01:08:07,090
Run.

776
01:08:32,310 --> 01:08:33,949
It was nothing.

777
01:08:36,619 --> 01:08:38,619
It was someone I met
for the first time,

778
01:08:41,590 --> 01:08:42,890
but he just...

779
01:08:44,289 --> 01:08:45,390
dug into my heart.

780
01:09:26,630 --> 01:09:29,000
(A Piece of Your Mind)

781
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:32,109
I shouldn't have done anything.

782
01:09:32,510 --> 01:09:35,239
Is there something
you want to ask Ha Won?

783
01:09:35,239 --> 01:09:36,939
I want to see him from afar.

784
01:09:38,109 --> 01:09:39,710
I won't run away next time.

785
01:09:40,210 --> 01:09:41,350
What next time?

786
01:09:42,020 --> 01:09:43,520
If I can apologize...

787
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:45,050
There's nothing to apologize for.

788
01:09:45,289 --> 01:09:47,119
I told you already that
it's too much for me.

789
01:09:48,119 --> 01:09:51,090
What do you think
got him through those 10 years?

790
01:09:51,529 --> 01:09:53,689
Let's go tomorrow.

